The issue seems to be occurring because the initial position is being set globally in the `OnEpisodeBegin()`, and it should be set locally to its own Training Area.

Instead of calculating the `initialPosition` directly in the `OnEpisodeBegin()`, set the `initialPosition` based on the Training Area position.

Modify the `OnEpisodeBegin()` to make the random position relative to the Training Area's position like this:

```csharp
public override void OnEpisodeBegin()
{
    rb.velocity = Vector2.zero;

    // Get Training Area position
    Vector3 trainingAreaPosition = foodSpawner.transform.position;

    // Calculate the random position relative to the Training Area
    float randomX = UnityEngine.Random.Range(-foodSpawner.spawnRange, foodSpawner.spawnRange) + trainingAreaPosition.x;
    float randomY = UnityEngine.Random.Range(-foodSpawner.spawnRange, foodSpawner.spawnRange) + trainingAreaPosition.y;

    initialPosition = new Vector3(randomX, randomY, 0);
    transform.position = initialPosition;
}
```

